                <div class="work-description">
                    <h2>About The Piece</h2>
                    <p><strong>HUNCH</strong> is a typographic exploration of instinct—where suspicion sharpens and clarity flickers into focus. Rather than creating a literal depiction of detective logic boards, I leaned into suggestion and visual metaphor to build an atmosphere of psychological tension. The word is fragmented yet grounded, hinting at the invisible string that connects scattered thoughts to a single pivotal realization.</p>
                    <p>The condensed sans serif typeface serves as a bold structure for the viewer to mentally inhabit—solid, urgent, and weighty. I used white lines and nodes sparingly, referencing evidence diagrams not as decoration but as a conceptual scaffolding. These elements form a quiet chaos: purposeful disorder that encourages the viewer to feel rather than decode. The arrangement guides the eye like a mental hunch—subtle, erratic, but ultimately leading somewhere.</p>
                    <p>A moment of positive recognition lives within the letter “C,” breaking pattern just enough to suggest a shift in perception. By working abstractly with shape, rhythm, and negative space, I aimed to echo the feeling of a gut instinct surfacing—not loud, but undeniable. This piece invites a slow read, asking the viewer to connect internal clues through feeling rather than fact.</p>
                </div>
